1
00:01:09,517 --> 00:01:10,717
I'm standing right in front of you

2
00:01:10,717 --> 00:01:11,807
But <i>We</i>'re the Empress

3
00:01:11,807 --> 00:01:12,717
So what?

4
00:01:59,847 --> 00:02:00,427
Your Majesty

5
00:02:03,717 --> 00:02:04,137
You

6
00:02:14,097 --> 00:02:14,927
Ye Nanchen

7
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:16,717
Ye Nanchen, what's wrong with you?

8
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:20,307
Ye Nanchen, Ye Nanchen, what's wrong with you?

9
00:02:21,007 --> 00:02:23,017
Don't push me away anymore

10
00:02:24,347 --> 00:02:26,177
Ye Nanchen, Ye Nanchen

11
00:02:26,677 --> 00:02:27,557
Imperial Physician

12
00:02:28,267 --> 00:02:29,137
Imperial Physician

13
00:02:34,137 --> 00:02:35,007
Doctor He

14
00:02:35,017 --> 00:02:37,427
Your Majesty, Mr. Ye has been poisoned

15
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:39,967
I used a golden needle to protect the heart meridian temporarily

16
00:02:40,217 --> 00:02:41,217
Can the poison be cured?

17
00:02:41,467 --> 00:02:42,677
This poison is made from seven kinds of poisonous leaves,

18
00:02:42,677 --> 00:02:45,517
seven poisonous flowers and seven insects. It is called Seven Star Poison

19
00:02:45,677 --> 00:02:47,057
If you use the wrong medicine for one time,

20
00:02:47,557 --> 00:02:49,097
the toxicity will be triggered

21
00:02:49,597 --> 00:02:50,967
I have no way to cure it

22
00:02:51,347 --> 00:02:53,887
We need to find an antidote as soon as possible, otherwise

23
00:02:54,307 --> 00:02:55,307
Otherwise what will happen?

24
00:02:56,557 --> 00:02:57,677
He will die from poison

25
00:02:59,387 --> 00:03:00,096
Your Majesty

26
00:03:00,307 --> 00:03:01,177
You leave first

27
00:03:01,517 --> 00:03:02,097
Yes

28
00:03:06,847 --> 00:03:09,717
Find out who poisoned him

29
00:03:09,887 --> 00:03:10,427
Yes

30
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:28,097
This is all your bad idea

31
00:03:28,097 --> 00:03:29,887
The woman actually agreed

32
00:03:30,097 --> 00:03:31,637
I am the Princess of the Northern Kingdom

33
00:03:31,677 --> 00:03:33,017
Do I really have to marry a male concubine?

34
00:03:33,887 --> 00:03:35,637
Just wait

35
00:03:36,057 --> 00:03:37,057
Wait for what?

36
00:03:43,517 --> 00:03:45,216
Greetings to Your Highness

37
00:03:45,467 --> 00:03:47,467
Greetings to the Princess

38
00:03:49,267 --> 00:03:50,806
The poison in Ye Nanchen took effect

39
00:03:51,217 --> 00:03:52,677
The Empress got furious

40
00:03:53,847 --> 00:03:54,637
See

41
00:03:55,307 --> 00:03:56,427
What we were waiting for comes

42
00:03:56,717 --> 00:03:57,927
Poisoned?

43
00:03:58,097 --> 00:03:59,387
I just asked for him

44
00:03:59,387 --> 00:04:00,887
And then he was poisoned

45
00:04:01,267 --> 00:04:03,056
She would rather destroy him than give him to me

46
00:04:04,427 --> 00:04:05,306
No

47
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:08,466
This is also one of your plans

48
00:04:08,557 --> 00:04:10,467
Before killing someone, you must destroy their will first

49
00:04:11,017 --> 00:04:13,216
She cares a lot about that male concubine

50
00:04:13,517 --> 00:04:16,556
Otherwise, she wouldn't have gone to Cold Palace to see him

51
00:04:17,347 --> 00:04:18,057
You can leave now

52
00:04:18,597 --> 00:04:19,267
Okay

53
00:04:33,717 --> 00:04:35,517
Will you really

54
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:39,807
die for <i>Us</i> every lifetime?

55
00:05:04,057 --> 00:05:05,467
I asked you not to get close to <i>Us,</i>

56
00:05:07,177 --> 00:05:08,517
but you didn't listen to <i>Us</i>

57
00:05:13,097 --> 00:05:13,927
Once

58
00:05:15,017 --> 00:05:16,017
<i>We</i> don't believe in fate

59
00:05:18,556 --> 00:05:20,136
<i>We</i> think man's effort can conquer nature

60
00:05:26,427 --> 00:05:28,347
But until <i>We</i> came to your world

61
00:05:30,057 --> 00:05:31,097
and met you,

62
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:35,557
<i>We </i>believe it

63
00:05:39,007 --> 00:05:40,307
<i>We</i> don't want you

64
00:05:41,557 --> 00:05:43,717
<i>We</i> don't want you to die again

65
00:05:53,597 --> 00:05:54,177
Your Majesty

66
00:05:55,217 --> 00:05:56,137
The Princess of the Northern Kingdom is outside the door

67
00:05:56,847 --> 00:05:58,007
She said Ye Nanchen is her man

68
00:05:58,597 --> 00:06:00,637
She asked to see him even if he has died

69
00:06:02,057 --> 00:06:03,677
Confine her to her living quarter

70
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:05,467
Without my permission,

71
00:06:06,467 --> 00:06:07,767
don't let her out even for one step

72
00:06:08,347 --> 00:06:08,807
Yes

73
00:06:10,307 --> 00:06:11,266
Let me go

74
00:06:11,347 --> 00:06:13,137
How dare you!

75
00:06:14,517 --> 00:06:16,177
Let me go. Go

76
00:06:38,517 --> 00:06:41,427
Lord Xue, why do you arrest me?

77
00:06:41,517 --> 00:06:43,267
You brought Ye Nanchen into the palace

78
00:06:43,847 --> 00:06:45,347
He is in danger now

79
00:06:45,557 --> 00:06:48,886
What does his life or death have to do with me?

80
00:06:49,267 --> 00:06:51,017
He is just a male concubine

81
00:06:51,217 --> 00:06:53,057
His life is worthless

82
00:06:53,307 --> 00:06:54,967
He is your master

83
00:06:56,427 --> 00:06:57,217
Southern Kingdom

84
00:06:57,217 --> 00:06:59,557
is a state that existed more than a thousand years ago

85
00:06:59,967 --> 00:07:02,427
Chen, you've been so emotionally unstable lately

86
00:07:02,427 --> 00:07:03,886
Is there something you are hiding from me?

87
00:07:04,017 --> 00:07:05,847
Is there such a person

88
00:07:05,847 --> 00:07:09,717
to whom you'd give all the good things you have?

89
00:07:10,517 --> 00:07:11,717
Master?

90
00:07:19,017 --> 00:07:20,137
I'm

91
00:07:20,887 --> 00:07:23,267
the general director in charge of palace affairs

92
00:07:49,467 --> 00:07:51,927
May Your Majesty live and reign for ten thousand years, ten thousand of ten thousand years!

93
00:07:52,637 --> 00:07:53,517
Your Highness

94
00:07:53,517 --> 00:07:54,847
We're siblings,

95
00:07:54,847 --> 00:07:56,017
no need for such formalities

96
00:07:56,887 --> 00:07:58,467
The ruler is the ruler and the minister is the minister

97
00:07:58,637 --> 00:08:00,967
The proper etiquette still needs to be maintained

98
00:08:01,057 --> 00:08:02,057
Second brother, you have always been

99
00:08:02,057 --> 00:08:04,266
the most calm one among us,

100
00:08:04,557 --> 00:08:06,266
always keeping yourself out of affairs

101
00:08:06,767 --> 00:08:08,887
I don't understand what Your Majesty means

102
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:23,307
<i>We</i> know

103
00:08:24,347 --> 00:08:26,427
The Crown Prince was wrongly accused

104
00:08:27,097 --> 00:08:28,717
Just because there is no evidence,

105
00:08:29,017 --> 00:08:30,517
<i>We</i> had to exile him to the frontier

106
00:08:30,967 --> 00:08:33,057
Being too softhearted is

107
00:08:33,677 --> 00:08:35,347
not an advantage for an emperor

108
00:08:35,427 --> 00:08:37,217
There are plenty of people coveting the throne

109
00:08:37,677 --> 00:08:38,557
Really?

110
00:08:41,057 --> 00:08:43,967
Are you one of them?
